and the red dots are TESS
expected TESS planets,

00:24:34.710 --> 00:24:37.380
you'll see so far we've got
all red dots, a few blue.

00:24:37.380 --> 00:24:40.690
There's the first black dot,
over 100 light-years away.

00:24:40.690 --> 00:24:44.210
Here's the Kepler targets.

