00:44:29.510 --> 00:44:54.040
[ Inaudible Question ]

00:44:54.040 --> 00:44:56.560 position:56%
So let me see if I can pull this up.

00:44:56.560 --> 00:44:58.280
So the question was,
the first exoplanets

00:44:58.280 --> 00:45:01.960
that were found were large
planets, and they were close

00:45:01.960 --> 00:45:05.750
to their own sun; they were close
in, these were the hot Jupiters.

00:45:05.750 --> 00:45:11.010
Have we gotten better or closer
to finding things that are more

00:45:11.010 --> 00:45:12.690
like our own solar system?

00:45:12.690 --> 00:45:15.880 position:56%
Well, the answer is, the short
answer is, yes, we've gotten better.

00:45:15.880 --> 00:45:20.010
Originally we found things that
were all up in this regime,

00:45:20.010 --> 00:45:21.950
but now you can see that
there's a lot of planets that are

00:45:21.950 --> 00:45:24.510 position:56%
in the same general area as Jupiter.

00:45:24.510 --> 00:45:26.560
There's a few that
get close to Saturn.

00:45:26.560 --> 00:45:29.160
There's a few scattered in
here with the rocky planets.

00:45:29.160 --> 00:45:31.400
So we are doing better,
but we have a ways to go.

00:45:31.400 --> 00:45:34.460
One of the fundamental
limitations is the fact

00:45:34.460 --> 00:45:37.450
that stars themselves
are not well behaved.

00:45:37.450 --> 00:45:41.450
Stars are intrinsically
noisy, if you've looked

00:45:41.450 --> 00:45:43.990
at sun spots or solar flares.

00:45:43.990 --> 00:45:47.280
All stars do that at some
level, in fact, our star is,

00:45:47.280 --> 00:45:49.500
in the grand scheme of
things, relatively quiet.

00:45:49.500 --> 00:45:53.480
So we try to make measurements of
these planets around other stars,

00:45:53.480 --> 00:45:57.900
we have to take into account the
fact that there's all this activity

00:45:57.900 --> 00:45:59.830
of the star that interferes
with out measurement.

00:45:59.830 --> 00:46:01.130
But we are getting better.

00:46:01.130 --> 00:46:04.870
It is unclear how far we
can go from the ground.

00:46:04.870 --> 00:46:08.170
It's unclear how far we can
go with these techniques.

00:46:08.170 --> 00:46:14.510 position:56%
But we're going to keep pushing that
until we get as far as we can go.

00:46:14.510 --> 00:46:37.040
